To use this expression, you can apply it to the property you want to animate. For example, if you want to apply it to the position property of a layer, select that layer, hit the P key to reveal the position property, and then add the expression to the position property by alt-clicking (or option-clicking on a Mac) on the stopwatch icon. 

Note that this expression uses two parameters, freq and decay, to control the frequency and decay of the bounce. You can adjust these values to create different types of bounce animations.

